lastfm.summary: Counting Blue Cars" is a song by the alternative rock band Dishwalla that appears on their 1995 album Pet Your Friends. It was Dishwalla's only hit song, making it onto the Billboard Hot 100 in 1996 through A&M Records. The song is recognizable by the line in the chorus, "Tell me all your thoughts on God ('cause I'd really like to meet her)". The song was featured in the 1999 film Eight Days a Week.
